50|$|In 2003 Israel was {{the area}} of ORTs largest operation, with 90,000 {{students}} educated or trained at ORT’s 159 schools, colleges and institutions, educating 25% of Israel’s hi-tech workforce. However in 2006 ORT Israel withdrew from <b>World</b> <b>ORT.</b> <b>World</b> <b>ORT</b> continues to work in Israel {{under the name of}} Kadima Mada-Educating for Life, working with the Israeli Ministry of Education, other Israeli ministries, regional councils and hospitals providing increased resources and improved facilities and schools equipment. <b>World</b> <b>ORT</b> raises funds through its membership organisations in different countries and through the Jewish Federations of North America (JFNA).|$|R
